{"architecture":{"frozen_components":["ConceptNet knowledge graph (external data source)"],"mechanism_tags":["knowledge-injection","synthetic-qa-generation","contrastive-learning","multi-hop-reasoning","mlm-scoring"],"seam_cell":"text","summary":"A two-stage framework for zero-shot commonsense question answering. Stage 1 synthesizes multi-hop QA pairs from knowledge graphs (ConceptNet) using two generation methods (compositive and conjunctive) that extract 2-hop paths and generate hard negative samples via linguistic templates. Stage 2 pre-trains RoBERTa-Large on the synthetic dataset using masked language modeling (MLM) scoring combined with InfoNCE contrastive loss, where QA pairs are concatenated and token-by-token MLM losses summed to rank candidates. At inference, lowest MLM score selects the answer.","trained_components":["RoBERTa-Large language model (pre-trained weights fine-tuned via contrastive pre-training)"]},"biblio":{"authors":[],"title":"Multi-hop Commonsense Knowledge Injection Framework for Zero-Shot Commonsense Question Answering","venue":null,"year":2023},"claims":[{"baseline":{"name":"Zero-shot fusion (Adapter) Kim et al. (2022)","value":68.2},"claim_id":"c1","compute_reported":false,"dataset":"CommonsenseQA (CSQA)","evidence":"claimed","evidence_ref":null,"metric":"accuracy","scale":{"params":355000000.0,"rungs_measured":1},"statement":"achieves state-of-art performance on CommonsenseQA with accuracy of 71.0%","type":"quantitative","unit":"percent","value":71.0},{"baseline":{"name":"RoBERTa-L (MR) Ma et al. (2021)","value":65.6},"claim_id":"c2","compute_reported":false,"dataset":"Multiple Choice Temporal commonsense (MC-TACO)","evidence":"claimed","evidence_ref":null,"metric":"accuracy","scale":{"params":355000000.0,"rungs_measured":1},"statement":"improves accuracy by approximately 5.3% on MC-TACO benchmark","type":"quantitative","unit":"percent","value":70.9},{"baseline":{"name":"Zero-shot fusion (Adapter) Kim et al. (2022)","value":72.5},"cla